1.1
log
@*** empty log message ***
@
text
@a0 15
This is a proto for a proposal to get adopted in Rishonomic.  It follows
the simplest and most general ideas expressed so far: establish a
very-difficult-to-modify rule, which contains language describing how
Risho is entirely subservient to Agora, and with a clause allowing Agora
to change Risho's ruleset at will.  No legislation is required within
Agora to match this.

This should be submitted as a Speedy proposal, which will limit the voting
period to 3 days.  It will require a 3/5 majority to pass; if there are
seven real Risho players, plus their Gnome vote, we will need at least
13 YES votes.  We should, however, consider the possibility that they
might realise the extent of the conspiracy, and get friends to register
and vote against the proposal.  If their Proposal 336 passes, we should
take advantage of it.

d7 2
a8 2
      nomics.  Agora is the overlord of Rishonomic by divine right.
      Rishonomic is not worthy to wash Agora's boots with its tongue.
d11 3
a13 3
      of its Proposals that expresses a desire to modify Rishonomic's
      ruleset, then the modifications it wishes occur as soon as the
      Speaker receives a copy of the Proposal from an Agora Player.
d20 3
a22 3
      retitled, renumbered, pushed, shoved, filed, stamped or debriefed
      by any means other than those required by this rule.  This rule
      takes precedence over all other rules.
@
